    public interface DescriptorEntitySet
extends Axiom
    This interface contains classes that can be used to instantiate EntitySets containing entities of a particular type. The entity types within the OWLOOP architecture are among the following:
    • DescriptorEntitySet.Individuals: type to describe a set of: [OWL-Individual].
    • DescriptorEntitySet.Concepts: type to describe a set of: [OWL-Class].
    • DescriptorEntitySet.Literals: type to describe a set of: [OWL-Literal] (i.e., data values).
    • DescriptorEntitySet.DataProperties: type to describe a set of: [OWL-DataProperty].
    • DescriptorEntitySet.ObjectProperties: type to describe a set of: [OWL-ObjectProperty].
    • DescriptorEntitySet.Restrictions: type to describe a set of: [OWL-Restriction].
    • DescriptorEntitySet.DataLinks: type to describe a set of: [An Expression along with an OWL-Literal] .
    • DescriptorEntitySet.ObjectLinks: type to describe a set of: [An Expression along with an OWL Individual].
